21.32	Nipkow_disk	Nipkow disk	A Nipkow disk (sometimes Anglicized as Nipkov disk), also known as scanning disk, is a mechanical, geometrically operating image scanning device, invented by Paul Gottlieb Nipkow. This scanning disk was a fundamental component in mechanical television through the 1920s.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/08/Nipkow_disk.svg/300px-Nipkow_disk.svg.png
